metrics.description: This is the total amount of space (in bytes) that would be consumed if the LUN is fully provisioned. This includes snapshots, attached snapshot LUNs and Metadata

metrics.name: Size Total
metrics.description: Host visible LUN size (in bytes)

metrics.name: Snapshot Space Allocated
metrics.description: This is the total amount of storage (in bytes) that has been allocated to the LUN for all the snapshots created of it. This does not include storage that is shared with the primary or any storage required for metadata. Any additional space used by attached snapshot LUNs associated with this LUN is included in this number

metrics.name: Snapshot Size Subscribed
metrics.description: This is the total amount of space (in bytes) that a LUN's snapshots currently consume as well as what they would consume if all base LUN data was overwritten

metrics.name: Overhead Subscribed Space
metrics.description: This is the total amount of storage (in bytes) that the Pool would need for metadata for the LUNs, SFs and snapshots in that Pool if they are fully subscribed

metrics.name: Overhead Space
metrics.description: This is the total amount of storage (in Bytes) that has been allocated from the Pool to store metadata

metrics.name: Size Free
metrics.description: Total size - used size

metrics.name: Subscribed Space
metrics.description: This is the total amount of space in the Pool that would be consumed if all of the Pools, LUNs, and SFs were fully provisioned. This includes snapshots, attached snapshot LUNs and Metadata

metrics.name: Capacity
metrics.description: User visible size of the pool (in Bytes)

metrics.name: Size Used
metrics.description: This is the total amount of storage (in bytes) that is currently allocated from this Pool. This includes storage required for data, metadata, primary LUNs, SFs, snapshots

metrics.name: Total Consumed Capacity
metrics.description: This is the total amount of storage (512-byte blocks) that is currently allocated from this Pool. This includes storage required for data, metadata, primary LUNs, SFs, snapshots

metrics.name: Snap Subscribed Space
metrics.description: This is the total amount of space (in bytes) that all snapshots currently consume as well as what they would consume if all of the base LUNs / SFs data was overwritten. Any additional space used by attached snapshot LUNs in this pool is included in this number

metrics.name: Snapshot Space
metrics.description: This is the total amount of storage (in bytes) that has been allocated from the Pool for all the snapshots created in the Pool. This does not include storage that is shared with the primary, storage required for metadata, or uncommitted storage
